{{Infobox language |name=Gehuo |nativename= |states=[[China]] |region=[[Yunnan]] |ethnicity=[[Hani people|Hani]] |speakers=? |date= |ref= |familycolor=Sino-Tibetan |fam2=([[Tibeto-Burman languages|Tibeto-Burman]]) |fam3=[[Lolo–Burmese languages|Lolo–Burmese]] |fam4=[[Loloish languages|Loloish]] |fam5=[[Hanoish languages|Southern Loloish]] |fam6=[[Hani languages|Hani]] |iso3=none |glotto=none }} '''Gehuo''' ({{zh|格活}}) is a [[Hanoish languages|Southern Loloish]] language of [[Yunnan]], China. It is spoken in Baima Shangzhai 白马上寨村, Yingpan Township 营盘乡, [[Jinping Miao, Yao, and Dai Autonomous County|Jinping County]] 金平县, Yunnan (Yang, et al. 2011).<ref name="Gehuo">[http://www.ynszxc.gov.cn/villagePage/vIndex.aspx?departmentid=189229 金平苗族瑶族傣族自治县营盘乡罗戈塘村委会白马上寨村]</ref> Their autonym is '''Hanni 含妮''', whereas the neighboring Hani people refer to them as Gehuo 格活 (Yang, et al. 2011:9). The Gehuo are also found in parts of [[Lüchun County]] and [[Yuanyang County, Yunnan]] (Yang, et al. 2011:5-6).
==Distribution== The ''Jinping County Ethnic Gazetteer'' (2013:89, 101)<ref>金平苗族瑶族傣族自治县民族志1979-2010. 金平苗族瑶族傣族自治県民族宗教事務局編. 雲南民族出版社. 2013年8月. {{ISBN|9787536757028}}</ref> reports that Gehe 格合 (Gehe 格河;<ref name="Almanac">''Jinping County Almanac'' (1994)</ref> Gehuo 格活; in Laomeng Township 老勐乡 their exonym is [[Angluo language|Angluo]] 昂珞) is spoken in Tongchang 铜厂, Yingpan 营盘, and Laomeng 老勐 townships, and comprised 2,563 households and 10,510 persons as of 2005.
