'''Moorthy Muthuswamy''' is an Indian-American nuclear physicist, writer and author.<ref>http://www.washingtontimes.com/news/2009/may/27/reversing-us-policy-in-afpak/</ref>
Moorthy has a doctoral degree in [[nuclear physics]] from [[Stony Brook University]], New York.<ref>http://inspirehep.net/record/345772/</ref> He has published books on [[political Islam]].<ref>http://www.washingtontimes.com/news/2009/may/27/reversing-us-policy-in-afpak/</ref>
His book "Defeating Political Islam: The New Cold War" was reviewed at [[Washington Times]] [http://www.washingtontimes.com/news/2009/may/27/reversing-us-policy-in-afpak/] and the [[Association for the Study of the Middle East and Africa]] [http://www.moorthymuthuswamy.com/Book%20Review%20List.html] and received praise from [[Geert Wilders]], [[Paul Eidelberg]], [[Gary Johnson]] and [[Robert Spencer (author)|Robert Spencer]].[http://www.moorthymuthuswamy.com/] It has a foreword by [[Steven Emerson|Steve Emerson]].
